We see that the graph of $y = 64 \sqrt{x} - x - 1$ is decreasing on the interval $(-1,0),$ and increasing on the interval $(0,\infty).$  Hence, the solutions to the inequality $64 \sqrt{r} - r - 1 \le 0$ are $r \in [-1,64].$

Therefore, the set of possible values of $r$ is $\boxed{[-1,64]}.$
